env PAGER=cat man timing_derate_incremental_multiply_accumulative_ mode
Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_derate_...umulative_mode(25.10)  timing_derate_...umulative_mode(25.10)

Name
       timing_derate_incremental_multiply_accumulative_mode

Syntax
       timing_derate_incremental_multiply_accumulative_mode {true | false}

       Default: false

       Controls  the overwrite or accumulative mode settings when the set_tim-
       ing_derate -multiply parameter is specified.

       When set to false, the last specified set_timing_derate -multiply  com-
       mand will overwrite the previous constraints at the same level.

       When  set  to  true,  all the values saved in history will be accumula-
       tively multiplied, when multiple -multiply settings  are  made  on  the
       same object.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

Examples
              * The following example shows that in overwrite mode, the multi-
                plicative adjustment will be updated to 0.5:

                set timing_derate_incremental_multiply_accumulative_mode false

                set_timing_derate -multiply 1.2

                set_timing_derate -multiply 0.5

              * The  following  example  shows  that in accumulative mode, the
                multiplicative adjustment will be updated to 1.2*0.5=0.6:

                set timing_derate_incremental_multiply_accumulative_mode true

                set_timing_derate -multiply 1.2

                set_timing_derate -multiply 0.5

